
Stuff I'd like:
	interactive mode
	buffered input mode


Interactive Mode:
	get it using the -i command line switch
	will display a prompt instead of reading from a file
	Will immediately execute your entered code

# ++++++++[>++++[>+>+<<-]>+>+>+<<<<-]>>.>+.>++.
Hi
<ok>
# 

	Should look something like that

Buffered input:
	use the -b command line switch
	use `scanf("%c", &c)` instead of `c = getc(stdin)` for keyboard input
	will echo typed characters

Read int-values instead of key-values:
	-n
	buffered input only
	keyboard input echoes to screen.
	The ',' command will use `scanf(" %i", &c)` instead of `scanf(" %c", &c)`

use it like:
$ bfi -i
$ bfi -ib
$ bfi -in
$ bfi -b source.bf
$ bfi -n source.bf


